//axhob_operation
{bust_knock}

NOTE: Probes the workload account's reachability via key-only SSH.
Used to confirm that a {burp_investiture}'s workload trust is currently
usable before dispatching real work, and used internally as the
final-step validation of {busn_garrison}.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burp_investiture}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burp_regime} profile exists at the given {burp_investiture} and its
referenced {burn_regime} profile is reachable.

//axhoq_precondition
{busn_garrison} has been run for this {burp_investiture} so that
{burc_workload_user} exists on the node and trusts the workload pubkey
derived from {burp_workload_key_file}.

//axhos_step
. *Open workload SSH*: connect as {burc_workload_user} using
{burp_workload_key_file}; key-auth only.

//axhos_step
. *Issue trivial command*: execute a no-op on the remote
(e.g., `true`) and observe the remote exit status.

//axhog_guarantee
No remote OS state was modified.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when the remote command returns 0 within the probe window.
Non-zero on connection refusal, authentication failure, remote-exec
failure, or probe-window timeout.

//axhob_operation
{bust_command_file}

NOTE: Executes the contents of a local command file on the remote node
as {burc_workload_user} and captures stdout, stderr, and the remote
exit status to {burd_output_dir}.
The remote shell is whichever shell-letter garrisoned the node; the
operator does not choose it at dispatch time.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burp_investiture}

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{busi_scribed_command_file}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burp_regime} profile exists at the given {burp_investiture} and is
{bust_knock}-responsive.

//axhoq_precondition
The local command file referenced as the dispatch input exists and is
readable by the calling user.

//axhos_step
. *Open workload session*: open an SSH session to {burc_workload_user}
using {burp_workload_key_file}.

//axhos_step
. *Stream command file*: feed the command-file contents to the remote
shell.

//axhos_step
. *Capture outputs*: write remote stdout, stderr, and the remote exit
status to {burd_output_dir}.

//axhog_guarantee
The complete remote stdout, stderr, and exit code are durably written
under {burd_output_dir} regardless of the remote command's success or
failure.

//axhoc_completion
Exit 0 when dispatch and capture both complete (independent of the
remote exit code).
Non-zero on SSH connection failure, capture-write failure, or transport
interruption.

//axhob_operation
{bust_interactive_session}

NOTE: Opens an interactive SSH session to {burc_workload_user} on the
node named by a {burp_investiture}.
Foreground operation; control returns to the station shell when the
operator exits the remote shell.

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{burp_investiture}

//axhoq_precondition
A {burp_regime} profile exists at the given {burp_investiture} and is
{bust_knock}-responsive.

//axhos_step
. *Hand control to SSH*: invoke the local SSH client interactively
against {burc_workload_user} using {burp_workload_key_file}.

//axhos_step
. *Wait for exit*: block until the operator exits the remote shell.

//axhog_guarantee
No artifact is written to {burd_output_dir} — interactive sessions
deliberately bypass dispatch capture.
No local profile is modified.

//axhoc_completion
Exit code mirrors the SSH client's exit code when the session ends
normally.
Non-zero on connection or authentication failure before the session
opens.
